<tr><td><div>

<font size="+4" color=#990000>Irregular verbs</font> also change at the <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>stem</strong></font> <br>
<br>
There are several types of irregular verbs, but basically, some verbs are <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>totally irregular</strong></font> and 
some will only be <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>partially irregular</strong></font>.  An example of a totally irregular ver is "ser":<br>
<table align="center" cellpadding=10" bgcolor="#D7EBD7">
<tr>
<td><div>yo</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>soy</strong></font></div></td>
<td width="50">&nbsp;</td>
<td><div>nosotros / nosotras</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>somos</strong></font></div></td></tr>
<tr>
<td><div>t&uacute;</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>eres</strong></font></div></td>
<td width="50">&nbsp;</td>
<td><div>vosotros</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>sois</strong></font></div></td></tr>

<tr>
<td valign="bottom"><div>&eacute;l / ella / usted</div></td>
<td valign="bottom"><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>es</strong></font></div></td>
<td width="50">&nbsp;</td>
<td valign="bottom"><div>ellos / ellas / ustedes </div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>son</strong></font></div></td>
<br>
</tr>
</table>

<br>
Note that the stem changes with no pattern and the endings do not match normal "-er" endings.



</div></td></tr>







